<i>nanny named Mrs. Featherbottom.</i>

00:39.005 --> 00:41.439
Who'd like a banger
in the mouth?

00:41.541 --> 00:46.774
Oh, right. I forgot. Here in the States
you call it a sausage in the mouth.

00:46.880 --> 00:50.976
- We just call it a sausage.
- <i>[Narrator] The family,</i>
<i>of course, knew it was Tobias...</i>

00:51.084 --> 00:52.608
<i>but the house had</i>
<i>never been cleaner.</i>

00:52.719 --> 00:55.381
Hello, young lady.
I haven't seen you in a week.

00:55.488 --> 00:58.889
<i>Oh. Right. That means</i>
<i>Mrs. Featherbottom isn't here.</i>

00:58.992 --> 01:01.586
Which means she didn't iron
my blouse...

01:01.694 --> 01:05.152
which means I don't have
anything to wear for my premiere.

01:05.265 --> 01:08.166
<i>The</i> premier-
of Canada.

01:08.268 --> 01:10.634
He's going out
with my gym teacher.

01:10.737 --> 01:13.228
<i>[Narrator] Maeby was actually</i>
<i>referring to the premiere of a film...</i>

01:13.339 --> 01:16.399
<i>from the studio</i>
<i>where she had conned her way into a job.</i>

01:16.509 --> 01:18.670
Hey, Jeff. Did you get
a chance to do coverage on...

01:18.778 --> 01:20.678
<i>Voices In America:</i>
<i>History In Prespective?</i>

01:20.780 --> 01:24.238
Yeah. I looked that up.
It's a ninth grade history textbook.

01:24.350 --> 01:28.787
Yeah. And if I don't get your report on it,
I won't be able to pass.

01:28.888 --> 01:32.847
On it.
Because I have a feeling it's a piece of- [Bleeps]

01:32.959 --> 01:35.928
<i>[Narrator] Unfortunately, thejob was</i>
<i>wreaking havoc with her language.</i>

01:36.029 --> 01:38.293
Maybe we just need a new-
[Bleeps] housekeeper.

01:38.398 --> 01:40.559
<i>Okay. I'm sure she would</i>
<i>have ironed it for you...</i>

01:40.667 --> 01:43.795
had you told her about it before
she changed out of her bloody work clothes.

01:43.903 --> 01:46.770
<i>But I am off then.</i>

01:49.375 --> 01:52.105
- <i>[Door Closes]</i>
- I gotta keep him trying. That is the job.

01:54.814 --> 01:56.782
Michael, what are you
doing tomorrow?

01:56.883 --> 02:00.114
Having my day ruined with
whatever you're about to ask me to do.

02:00.220 --> 02:04.122
It's my wedding anniversary,
and Oscar wants to throw me a party.

02:04.224 --> 02:06.852
He is aware that
he's not married to you, right?

02:06.960 --> 02:10.794
<i>[Narrator] In fact, Oscar had started to perceive</i>
<i>that Lucille was pulling away from him.</i>

02:10.896 --> 02:14.298
Not now.
It's my time of the month.

02:14.400 --> 02:19.133
Not now. I don't want to risk
having a baby. It could kill me.

02:19.239 --> 02:22.504
- <i>[Narrator] So he went to Buster for advice.</i>
- I think she misses my brother.

02:22.609 --> 02:25.806
- My father?
- Yes? I mean, yes.

02:25.912 --> 02:29.075
- Maybe I should throw her an anniversary party.
- [Gasps] Oh.

02:29.182 --> 02:32.982
So when he doesn't show, she'll realize that
you were the one who was always there for us.

02:33.086 --> 02:35.714
Well, I was thinking one more party,
and then I'd move out.

02:35.822 --> 02:37.915
But no.
I like your plan better.

02:38.024 --> 02:40.891
The only problem is we know he's-
he's around somewhere.

02:40.994 --> 02:43.155
Well, he didn't return
when I lost my hand.

02:43.263 --> 02:46.096
But you-
you not only embrace it...

02:46.199 --> 02:49.327
but I saw you kissing it
while you thought I was sleeping.

02:49.435 --> 02:52.666
- [Squeaking Sound]
- <i>[Vocalizing]</i>

02:52.772 --> 02:54.740
<i>[Singing]</i>

02:54.841 --> 02:58.174
