<i>introduced a puppet.</i>

03:17.463 --> 03:20.364
- Can I tell you somethin', my man?
- Sure, Franklin.

03:20.466 --> 03:24.596
<i>You are one cool</i>- 
<i>[Bleeps]</i>

03:24.704 --> 03:29.573
Speakin' of mothers,
let me give that oatmeal some brown sugar.

03:29.676 --> 03:33.077
- Get off my wife, you bastard!
- Oh, man. What's the matter with you?

03:33.179 --> 03:35.147
Franklin said some things
Whitey wasn't ready to hear.

03:35.248 --> 03:39.207
Gob, weren't you also mercilessly beaten
outside of a club in Torrance for that act?

03:39.319 --> 03:42.584
He also said some things that
African-Americany wasn't ready to hear either.

03:42.689 --> 03:44.884
You know, Mom,
we have no idea where Dad is.

03:44.991 --> 03:46.891
How's he gonna
hear about the party?

03:46.993 --> 03:49.484
Why do you have
the baby monitor out?

03:49.596 --> 03:52.724
- [Michael] I'm, uh, listening in-
- She wants her man back.

03:52.832 --> 03:56.097
- On my son.
- Yo, man. You're gonna get your
sorry white ass thrown in jail.

03:56.202 --> 03:59.137
I said that's enough.

03:59.239 --> 04:02.265
<i>[Narrator] Michael came up with an excuse</i>
<i>he knew his mother would understand.</i>

04:02.375 --> 04:04.741
I'm listening in on my son.

04:04.844 --> 04:07.438
I'm a little worried
about his girlfriend, Ann.

04:07.547 --> 04:10.243
<i>My advice, get one of those teddy bears</i>
<i>with the cameras in them.</i>

04:10.350 --> 04:14.343
I had one in Buster's room to make sure
he wasn't getting too serious with anyone.

04:14.454 --> 04:18.481
As it turned out,
he got too serious with the teddy bear.

04:18.591 --> 04:23.028
I'll see you
at the anniversary party.

04:23.129 --> 04:25.620
- Gangy's having an anniversary party?
- Seems that way.

04:25.732 --> 04:29.190
- Is Franklin gonna be there?
- See that, Mike? Kids love Franklin.

04:29.302 --> 04:32.328
I just don't want him to point out
my cracker ass in front of Ann.

04:34.474 --> 04:36.442
Imagine what he'd say
about her.

04:36.542 --> 04:39.636
So you <i>were</i> listening in
on George Michael.

04:39.746 --> 04:42.180
Can you believe
what he asked me this morning?

04:42.282 --> 04:44.614
Do you think my mom's
engagement ring is still around?

04:44.717 --> 04:48.551
Of course it is. Your father would never
part with something so precious.

04:48.655 --> 04:53.456
<i>[Narrator] In fact, Lindsay was currently</i>
<i>wearing it on her middle toe, roast beef.</i>

04:53.559 --> 04:55.857
I'm thinking of asking Ann
to get pre-engaged.

04:55.962 --> 05:00.023
- You are?
- Yeah. I feel like God moved her
here from Ohio to be with me.

05:00.133 --> 05:03.296
- <i>[George] Her?</i>
- Well, that's the first I've heard of this.

05:03.403 --> 05:06.839
- Well, then who said "Her?"
- Me. That was-That was me.

05:06.939 --> 05:09.499
But, um, her?

05:09.609 --> 05:11.975
Look, it's just a pre-engagement.
It's exciting.

05:12.078 --> 05:13.705
You know,
it's young love.

05:13.813 --> 05:16.748
I had it once.
A man I loved-

05:18.418 --> 05:22.013
- Here's young Maeby's blouse.
- And then things took a turn somehow.

05:22.121 --> 05:25.818
<i>Master Bluth.</i>
<i>I haven't seen you in a week's time.</i>

05:25.925 --> 05:28.985
Actually, you tried to put a banger
in my mouth this morning.

05:29.095 --> 05:32.462
Oh, was it this morn-
Well, I'm sorry.

05:32.565 --> 05:36.331
- I'm just so exhausted.
- So I'm just gonna talk to my son.

05:36.436 --> 05:39.496
I'm gonna tell him that I'm against this.
I don't like her.

05:39.605 --> 05:42.574
You know, maybe if you
stop judging her, he'd trust you.

05:42.675 --> 05:46.611
Look, if you say no,
you're just gonna drive him right to her.

05:46.713 --> 05:48.943
<i>Hey, Dad.</i>
<i>Can you drive me to Ann's?</i>

05:49.048 --> 05:51.346
N-N-N-

05:51.451 --> 05:55.046
- Y-Yes.
- Great. I'll wait in the car.

05:55.154 --> 05:57.452
I don't think that worked.

05:57.557 --> 06:02.688
<i>[Narrator] Meanwhile, Gob went to check on</i>
<i>the one friend who didn't mind having him around.</i>

06:02.795 --> 06:05.628
<i>[George]</i>
<i>Get your loser hand out of my ass.</i>

06:05.732 --> 06:08.360
- Hello, Son.
- Oh, Dad. I thought- Dad?

06:08.468 --> 06:11.494
This is where you've been hi- Michael.

06:11.604 --> 06:13.572
I just came back
because of your mother.

06:13.673 --> 06:16.198
She's with my brother
on my anniversary.

06:16.309 --> 06:18.209
But I got an idea
from George Michael.

06:18.311 --> 06:20.245
I need to recommit myself
to your mother.

06:20.346 --> 06:23.247
- Her?
- But you gotta get me into that party.

06:23.349 --> 06:25.283
Then you gotta
take me to this church.

06:25.385 --> 06:27.512
I found this brochure
that Ann left behind.

06:27.620 --> 06:30.088
That's gonna be tough.
I'm not really all that invited.

06:30.189 --> 06:32.623
I got it all worked out,
but I need a limousine.

06:32.725 --> 06:35.250
L- I can do this, Dad.
I'm gonna make you proud.

06:35.361 --> 06:37.727
Never too late to start.

06:37.830 --> 06:43.063
<i>[Narrator] And Michael drove to Ann's house,</i>
<i>where he finally got to meet Ann's parents.</i>

06:43.169 --> 06:45.797
This is my father,
Pastor Terry Veal.

06:45.905 --> 06:49.397
- Hello.
- Oh, Pastor. I didn't know. You didn't tell me.

06:49.509 --> 06:51.409
- I told you.
- No, you didn't.

06:51.511 --> 06:54.105
People treat you so differently
when they find out you're a man of God.

06:54.213 --> 06:57.774
- Oh, believe me, I know.
- Oh, are you a churchgoing man?

06:57.884 --> 06:59.613
I am.

06:59.719 --> 07:02.654
Sometimes. Yes.
I don't go religiously.

07:02.755 --> 07:04.780
I mean,
I'm not a nut about it.

07:04.891 --> 07:09.191
Because there is no such thing
as a nut when it comes to religion, Pastor.

07:09.295 --> 07:11.627
I've met a few.

07:11.731 --> 07:14.529
I'm sure if you look a bit closer
you'll find some very earnest people...

07:14.634 --> 07:16.534
that are just
doing their best.

07:16.636 --> 07:18.536
<i>- What are you doin', Dad?</i>
- I'm not sure.

07:18.638 --> 07:22.506
Why don't you kids run along and let us
get to know each other a bit better? Thank you.

07:22.608 --> 07:25.099
- Maybe I should get my wife. Honey.
- Okay.

07:25.211 --> 07:27.111
<i>[Pastor Veal]</i>
<i>This is George Michael's father.</i>

07:27.213 --> 07:30.444
<i>This is your wife.</i>
<i>Didn't</i>- <i>Didn't realize you could remarry.</i>

07:30.550 --> 07:33.678
- What?
- Is this Ann's mother?

07:33.786 --> 07:35.947
- I'm Mrs. Veal.
- I'm sorry. I just-

07:36.055 --> 07:38.387
I did not expect
somebody so young.

07:38.491 --> 07:41.119
Next you're gonna say
how Ann and I can be sisters.

07:41.227 --> 07:43.491
No, I'd never say that.

07:43.596 --> 07:45.291
Listen, I'm here because...

07:45.398 --> 07:49.061
I think my son might be planning on
asking your daughter to get pre-engaged.

07:49.168 --> 07:51.329
- <i>Oh, my gosh.</i>
- Oh, my gosh.

07:51.437 --> 07:53.962
Well, that is something
to celebrate.

07:54.073 --> 07:56.564
Can we open up
some sparkling apple cider?

07:56.676 --> 07:59.645
- No.
- Oh, did you want us to
go down to the liquor store...

07:59.745 --> 08:01.645
and get you some liquor?

08:01.747 --> 08:03.806
No. Don't you think
they're a bit too young?

08:03.916 --> 08:05.645
Oh, we got serious
around his age.

08:05.751 --> 08:07.844
Who can blame you?
You gotta lock that down.

08:07.954 --> 08:10.149
But I'm not quite sure
that they're ready.

08:10.256 --> 08:13.225
Michael, in my experience,
there is no recipe for a perfect match.

08:13.326 --> 08:15.590
<i>It takes the love</i>
<i>of two families.</i>

08:15.695 --> 08:17.856
Well, you haven't met
my family.

08:17.964 --> 08:21.866
<i>[Narrator] And that's when Michael devised</i>
<i>a new plan to win the Veals'disapproval.</i>

08:21.968 --> 08:24.402
You haven't met my family.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.529
You should meet my family.

08:26.639 --> 08:28.732
We're gonna be having
an anniversary party.

08:28.841 --> 08:30.866
[Pastor Veal]
What a wonderful surprise.

08:30.977 --> 08:33.912
We would love to witness
a celebration of their love.

08:34.013 --> 08:35.981
That would be
a wonderful surprise.

08:36.082 --> 08:38.277
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>But he did want a little bit of insurance.</i>

08:38.384 --> 08:43.082
Hey, Gob.
Mom wants Franklin at the party.

08:43.188 --> 08:45.623
Yeah. What?

08:45.725 --> 08:49.058
No, no, no. I don't want to talk-
Hey, Franklin.

08:54.166 --> 08:57.465
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Lucille was setting up for the anniversary party...</i>

08:57.570 --> 08:59.731
<i>that she didn't expect</i>
<i>her husband to attend.</i>

08:59.839 --> 09:02.535
- <i>[Lucille] Where's the food?</i>
- Sorry. Just stuffing the mushroom.

09:02.642 --> 09:05.975
<i>You realize that's Tobias,</i>
<i>don't you?</i>

09:06.078 --> 09:08.478
If he's gonna raid my closet,
he's gonna work for it.

09:08.581 --> 09:12.210
- What happened to his ankle?
- <i>[Narrator] Tobias had attempted an entrance...</i>

09:12.318 --> 09:14.218
<i>that he hoped</i>
<i>would enchant his daughter.</i>

09:14.320 --> 09:16.288
[Singing In Falsetto]

09:16.389 --> 09:19.381
Ohhhh!

09:19.492 --> 09:22.825
We shan't be telling
your mother this, shan't we?

09:22.929 --> 09:27.127
Maybe you can point out to your mother
that your father hasn't arrived yet.

09:28.167 --> 09:32.263
Hmm. So, my father's
not here.

09:32.371 --> 09:35.135
Maybe he is.

09:38.544 --> 09:42.002
Ann just called. They had a predawn mass,
and then they're gonna go to mass, so-

09:42.114 --> 09:45.083
Well, Ann's got
a great deal of mass.

09:45.184 --> 09:48.153
Anyway, I hope
that the Veals like us.

09:48.254 --> 09:50.313
Why don't you go top off
your Gangy? Thanks.

09:50.423 --> 09:52.448
Wait a minute.
You invited the Veals?

09:52.558 --> 09:54.788
Only so that they'll
disapprove of us.

09:54.894 --> 09:57.089
I gotta kill this
pre-engagement somehow.

09:57.196 --> 09:59.756
And after Mom's second vodka,
and after Buster's second juice box...

09:59.865 --> 10:02.095
they're gonna forbid Ann
from even seeing my son...

10:02.201 --> 10:05.170
much less taking his ring,
and I'm still the good guy.

10:05.271 --> 10:09.332
So the devout religious family-
they're the bad guys?

10:09.442 --> 10:11.501
You'll understand when Maeby
starts getting proposals.

10:11.611 --> 10:14.171
<i>[Narrator]</i>
<i>Actually, Maeby had given two that day.</i>

10:14.280 --> 10:16.612
<i>I'm sorry. I can't read</i>
<i>what you wrote on this buck slip.</i>

10:16.716 --> 10:18.877
You've got the handwriting
of a 15-year-old.

10:18.985 --> 10:21.283
